title.narrative: UNICEF staff and partners have capacity to effectively plan, design, monitor and evaluate programmes

description.narrative: By integrating humanitarian action in the multi-year work plans, coherence across humanitarian and development interventions was strengthened. Programme staff improved monitoring because of high-level effort put into work planning, which was translated into better-quality agreements with partners. UNICEF conducted in total 507 (as of 15 Dec 2019) out of 307 planned programmatic visits (PVs) (165%) exceeding the minimum requirement to ensure results for children are delivered especially in hard-to-reach locations. Four evaluations have been finalized with management responses. In addition, UNICEF continued to play leadership role in the implementation and monitoring of UN Cooperation Framework (UNCF) in South Sudan. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:17/01/2020
